laboratory_examinations.findings: Low calcium level at presentation: 7.9 mg/dl (Normal range: 8–10.5 mg/dl), improved to 9.7 mg/dl at 12 days old for sibling 2.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Sibling 2: Serum calcium increased from 7.2 mg/dl (4 days old) to 7.7 mg/dl (5 days old), then to 9.7 mg/dl (12 days old).

laboratory_examinations.findings: PTH level was elevated: 580 pg/ml (Normal range: 10–65 pg/ml).
Elevated alkaline phosphatase: 741 U/L (Normal range: 110–400 U/L).
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: In sibling 1, alkaline phosphatase increased from 741 to 3363 U/L during the first week of treatment.

laboratory_examinations.findings: 1,25OHD level: 46 pg/ml (Normal range: 15–75 pg/ml), which was inappropriately normal considering hypocalcemia.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Sister 2: 1,25OHD was normal at 25 pg/ml while serum calcium was low.
